(revision position with no terminator, so if a script runs git log "$rev" and $rev starts with a) Tj
T*
(dash, git parses it as an option. From the commit that introduced --end-of-options : But that) Tj
T*
(doesn?t work for the revision parser, because -- is already meaningful there: it separates) Tj
